<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-09-14T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-09-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="34" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860f.51/435: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-14T16:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">September 14,
                                        1925—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 14—3
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>52. Your 43, my 50. Commercial attaché reports that Zell of New York
                            Trust Company made positive statement to him that credit of $12,000,000
                            had actually been made to Czechoslovak Banking Office. This statement
                            was made by Zell because of his interest in trying to ascertain if
                            Federal Reserve Bank had made similar credit.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Einstein</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>